<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="File.php" src="/usr/local/pear/share/pear/PHP/CodeSniffer/File.php"><scope doc="A PHP_CodeSniffer_File object represents a PHP source file and the tokens&#10;associated with it.&#10;&#10;It provides a means for traversing the token stack, along with&#10;other token related operations. If a PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniff finds and error or&#10; warning within a PHP_CodeSniffer_File, you can raise an error using the&#10; addError() or addWarning() methods.&#10;&#10;&lt;b&gt;Token Information&lt;/b&gt;&#10;&#10;Each token within the stack contains information about itself:&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;  array(&#10;   'code'       =&gt; 301,       // the token type code (see token_get_all())&#10;   'content'    =&gt; 'if',      // the token content&#10;   'type'       =&gt; 'T_IF',    // the token name&#10;   'line'       =&gt; 56,        // the line number when the token is located&#10;   'column'     =&gt; 12,        // the column in the line where this token&#10;                              // starts (starts from 1)&#10;   'level'      =&gt; 2          // the depth a token is within the scopes open&#10;   'conditions' =&gt; array(     // a list of scope condition token&#10;                              // positions =&gt; codes that&#10;                    2 =&gt; 50,  // openened the scopes that this token exists&#10;                    9 =&gt; 353, // in (see conditional tokens section below)&#10;                   ),&#10;  );&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;b&gt;Conditional Tokens&lt;/b&gt;&#10;&#10;In addition to the standard token fields, conditions contain information to&#10;determine where their scope begins and ends:&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;  array(&#10;   'scope_condition' =&gt; 38, // the token position of the condition&#10;   'scope_opener'    =&gt; 41, // the token position that started the scope&#10;   'scope_closer'    =&gt; 70, // the token position that ended the scope&#10;  );&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;The condition, the scope opener and the scope closer each contain this&#10;information.&#10;&#10;&lt;b&gt;Parenthesis Tokens&lt;/b&gt;&#10;&#10;Each parenthesis token (T_OPEN_PARENTHESIS and T_CLOSE_PARENTHESIS) has a&#10;reference to their opening and closing parenthesis, one being itself, the&#10;other being its opposite.&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;  array(&#10;   'parenthesis_opener' =&gt; 34,&#10;   'parenthesis_closer' =&gt; 40,&#10;  );&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;Some tokens can &quot;own&quot; a set of parenthesis. For example a T_FUNCTION token&#10;has parenthesis around its argument list. These tokens also have the&#10;parenthesis_opener and and parenthesis_closer indices. Not all parenthesis&#10;have owners, for example parenthesis used for arithmetic operations and&#10;function calls. The parenthesis tokens that have an owner have the following&#10;auxiliary array indices.&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;  array(&#10;   'parenthesis_opener' =&gt; 34,&#10;   'parenthesis_closer' =&gt; 40,&#10;   'parenthesis_owner'  =&gt; 33,&#10;  );&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;Each token within a set of parenthesis also has an array indice&#10;'nested_parenthesis' which is an array of the&#10;left parenthesis =&gt; right parenthesis token positions.&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;  'nested_parenthesis' =&gt; array(&#10;                            12 =&gt; 15&#10;                            11 =&gt; 14&#10;                           );&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;b&gt;Extended Tokens&lt;/b&gt;&#10;&#10;PHP_CodeSniffer extends and augments some of the tokens created by&#10;&lt;i&gt;token_get_all()&lt;/i&gt;. A full list of these tokens can be seen in the&#10;&lt;i&gt;Tokens.php&lt;/i&gt; file.&#10;&#10;@category  PHP&#10;@package   PHP_CodeSniffer&#10;@author    Greg Sherwood &lt;gsherwood@squiz.net&gt;&#10;@author    Marc McIntyre &lt;mmcintyre@squiz.net&gt;&#10;@copyright 2006-2012 Squiz Pty Ltd (ABN 77 084 670 600)&#10;@license   https://github.com/squizlabs/PHP_CodeSniffer/blob/master/licence.txt BSD Licence&#10;@version   Release: 1.4.6&#10;@link      http://pear.php.net/package/PHP_CodeSniffer" ilk="class" line="117" lineend="2871" name="PHP_CodeSniffer_File"><variable attributes="private" citdl="string" doc="The absolute path to the file associated with this object.&#10;&#10;@var string" line="125" name="_file" /><variable attributes="public" citdl="string" doc="The EOL character this file uses.&#10;&#10;@var string" line="132" name="eolChar" /><variable attributes="public" citdl="PHP_CodeSniffer" doc="The PHP_CodeSniffer object controlling this run.&#10;&#10;@var PHP_CodeSniffer" line="139" name="phpcs" /><variable attributes="public" citdl="tokenizer" doc="The tokenizer being used for this file.&#10;&#10;@var object" line="146" name="tokenizer" /><variable attributes="public" citdl="string" doc="The tokenizer being used for this file.&#10;&#10;@var string" line="153" name="tokenizerType" /><variable attributes="public" citdl="int" doc="The number of tokens in this file.&#10;&#10;Stored here to save calling count() everywhere.&#10;&#10;@var int" line="162" name="numTokens" /><variable attributes="private" citdl="array" doc="The tokens stack map.&#10;&#10;Note that the tokens in this array differ in format to the tokens&#10;produced by token_get_all(). Tokens are initially produced with&#10;token_get_all(), then augmented so that it's easier to process them.&#10;&#10;@var array()&#10;@see Tokens.php" line="174" name="_tokens" /><variable attributes="private" citdl="array" doc="The errors raised from PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniffs.&#10;&#10;@var array()&#10;@see getErrors()" line="182" name="_errors" /><variable attributes="private" citdl="array" doc="The warnings raised form PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniffs.&#10;&#10;@var array()&#10;@see getWarnings()" line="190" name="_warnings" /><variable attributes="private" citdl="bool" doc="Record the errors and warnings raised.&#10;&#10;@var bool" line="197" name="_recordErrors" /><variable attributes="private" citdl="array" doc="And array of lines being ignored by PHP_CodeSniffer.&#10;&#10;@var array()" line="204" name="_ignoredLines" /><variable attributes="private" citdl="int" doc="The total number of errors raised.&#10;&#10;@var int" line="211" name="_errorCount" /><variable attributes="private" citdl="int" doc="The total number of warnings raised.&#10;&#10;@var int" line="218" name="_warningCount" /><variable attributes="private" citdl="array" doc="An array of sniffs listening to this file's processing.&#10;&#10;@var array(PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniff)" line="225" name="_listeners" /><variable attributes="private" citdl="string" doc="The class name of the sniff currently processing the file.&#10;&#10;@var string" line="232" name="_activeListener" /><variable attributes="private" citdl="array" doc="An array of sniffs being processed and how long they took.&#10;&#10;@var array()" line="239" name="_listenerTimes" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="array" doc="An array of extensions mapping to the tokenizer to use.&#10;&#10;This value gets set by PHP_CodeSniffer when the object is created.&#10;&#10;@var array" line="248" name="tokenizers" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="array" doc="An array of rules from the ruleset.xml file.&#10;&#10;This value gets set by PHP_CodeSniffer when the object is created.&#10;It may be empty, indicating that the ruleset does not override&#10;any of the default sniff settings.&#10;&#10;@var array" line="259" name="ruleset" /><scope attributes="public __ctor__" doc="Constructs a PHP_CodeSniffer_File.&#10;&#10;@param string          $file       The absolute path to the file to process.&#10;@param array(string)   $listeners  The initial listeners listening&#10;                                   to processing of this file.&#10;@param array           $tokenizers An array of extensions mapping&#10;                                   to the tokenizer to use.&#10;@param array           $ruleset    An array of rules from the&#10;                                   ruleset.xml file.&#10;@param PHP_CodeSniffer $phpcs      The PHP_CodeSniffer object controlling&#10;                                   this run.&#10;&#10;@throws PHP_CodeSniffer_Exception If the register() method does&#10;                                  not return an array." ilk="function" line="278" lineend="300" name="__construct" signature="__construct(string $file, array $listeners, array $tokenizers, array $ruleset, PHP_CodeSniffer $phpcs)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="278" name="file" /><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="278" name="listeners" /><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="278" name="tokenizers" /><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="278" name="ruleset" /><variable citdl="PHP_CodeSniffer" ilk="argument" line="278" name="phpcs" /><variable citdl="phpcs.cli.getCommandLineValues()" line="291" name="cliValues" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Sets the name of the currently active sniff.&#10;&#10;@param string $activeListener The class name of the current sniff.&#10;&#10;@return void" ilk="function" line="310" lineend="314" name="setActiveListener" signature="void setActiveListener(string $activeListener)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="310" name="activeListener" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Adds a listener to the token stack that listens to the specific tokens.&#10;&#10;When PHP_CodeSniffer encounters on the the tokens specified in $tokens,&#10;it invokes the process method of the sniff.&#10;&#10;@param PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniff $listener The listener to add to the&#10;                                       listener stack.&#10;@param array(int)            $tokens   The token types the listener wishes to&#10;                                       listen to.&#10;&#10;@return void" ilk="function" line="330" lineend="342" name="addTokenListener" signature="void addTokenListener(PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniff $listener, array $tokens)"><variable citdl="PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniff" ilk="argument" line="330" name="listener" /><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="330" name="tokens" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="332" name="token" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Removes a listener from listening from the specified tokens.&#10;&#10;@param PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniff $listener The listener to remove from the&#10;                                       listener stack.&#10;@param array(int)            $tokens   The token types the listener wishes to&#10;                                       stop listen to.&#10;&#10;@return void" ilk="function" line="355" lineend="373" name="removeTokenListener" signature="void removeTokenListener(PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniff $listener, array $tokens)"><variable citdl="PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniff" ilk="argument" line="355" name="listener" /><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="355" name="tokens" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="359" name="token" /><variable line="365" name="pos" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="365" name="value" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the token stack for this file.&#10;&#10;@return array()" ilk="function" line="381" lineend="385" name="getTokens" returns="array" signature="array getTokens()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Starts the stack traversal and tells listeners when tokens are found.&#10;&#10;@param string $contents The contents to parse. If NULL, the content&#10;                        is taken from the file system.&#10;&#10;@return void" ilk="function" line="396" lineend="569" name="start" signature="void start(string $contents = null)"><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="396" name="contents" /><variable citdl="string" line="548" name="error" /><variable citdl="listenerData" line="458" name="listener" /><variable citdl="token" line="446" name="tokenType" /><variable citdl="array()" line="476" name="replacements" /><variable line="516" name="col" /><variable citdl="explode()" line="429" name="sniffP